{{Wiktionary|annealing}} '''Annealing''' may refer to:
* [[Annealing (metallurgy)]], a heat treatment that alters the microstructure of a material causing changes in properties such as strength, hardness, and ductility * [[Annealing (glass)]], heating a piece of glass to remove stress * [[Annealing (biology)]], in genetics, means for complementary sequences of single-stranded DNA or RNA to pair by hydrogen bonds to form a double-stranded polynucleotide * [[Simulated annealing]], a numerical optimization technique for searching for a solution in a space otherwise too large for ordinary search methods to yield results * [[Quantum annealing]], a method for finding solutions to combinatorial optimisation problems and ground states of glassy systems using quantum fluctuations
{{disambiguation}}
